{
  "suite": "dfunc_kana_folding_probes",
  "description": "Mac Excel ja-JP D-functions (DSUM/DCOUNT/DGET/DAVERAGE/DMAX/DMIN) flow criterion text-equality through the same matcher that COUNTIF uses, so the kana fold from criteria.cpp should already cover the criterion-cell side. What is unverified is whether Mac also folds on the two header paths: (1) the `field` text argument resolved against database headers in resolve_field_column, and (2) the criteria-block header row resolved against database headers in find_db_column. These probes pin Mac's behaviour empirically before deciding whether database_lazy.cpp needs the same fold.\n",
